a united airlines jetliner carrying 147 people had to make an 
emergency landing sunday in new orleans when a hydraulic system 
failed and an eastern airlines plane made a unscheduled landing in 
texas after an engine shut down authorities said 
no injuries were reported in either incident 
emergency crews were waiting on the runway at new orleans 
international airport when flight 974 a boeing 727 en route from 
new orleans to chicago touched down at 124 pm cdt said united 
spokeswoman deborah jones in chicago 
the system failure had occurred about 25 minutes into the 
flight and the plane turned around and came back officials said 
as is the case in a situation like this there was equipment 
called out she said it wasnt needed 
it landed routinely and was towed back to the gate jones 
said losing the asystem would keep it from being maneuverable 
enough to move on its own once it landed 
hydraulic failure was blamed for the crash of a united airlines 
dc10 in sioux city iowa two months ago killing 112 people 
in amarillo texas the eastern airlines l1011 jet traveling 
from los angeles to atlanta with 230 passengers made an unscheduled 
landing after the no 2 engine shut down over texas said richard 
mccollum assistant airport manager 
mechanics were looking into a possible fuelline leak 
